comment: Equality for ALL includes men. What equality for ALL means to me is that we will see a day when an abused man can be heard and validated - not blamed for his own suffering. If a woman is abused by a man and we hear her abuser claim that it was her fault or that he didn't abuse her, we side with the woman. If the tables are turned, we still side with the woman and the man is left with no justice. I watched my father go through two abusive relationships with women and he never asked for help because he knew that nobody would believe him. I was also abused by these women and never felt like I would be believed, either. Equality for ALL is understanding that women are capable of the same things that men are and vice versa, because that's the truth.
